Huawei has unveiled the latest version of its P Smart smartphone in South Africa. The device is aimed at the mid-range market, offering impressive specifications at an attractive price point. Design changes compared to last year’s version of the device include a bezel-less display with a “dew drop” notch design. The P Smart 2019 also boasts more powerful cameras than the previous year’s model, with a dual-camera system on the back and a 16MP front-facing camera. This refreshed model features 64GB of internal storage with the option of expandable storage. Huawei said the P Smart 2019 will be available from local operators on 1 February and will be priced from R279 per month. The smartphone will be available in two colours – Black and Aurora – and has a recommended price tag of R4,999.